<http://www.cvlonghorns.de>
<cvlonghorns@aol.com>

[The 3 Swiss cantons involved can be identified on the map at
<http://images.switzerland.isyours.com/images/rg.maps.cantons.pdf>. - CopyEd.MJ

According to the most recent French information bulletin, dated 4 Sep
2008, the number of BTV-8 cases resulting from the virus circulation
during 2008, has reached 10 800 (the number of BTV-1 cases was 255).
See the report (in French), with a map, at
<http://agriculture.gouv.fr/sections/thematiques/sante-protection-animaux/maladies-animales/fievre-catarrhale-ovine/fichier-telecharger-7/downloadFile/FichierAttache_9_f0/pds_040908.pdf>.


The Swiss forecast of outbreaks expected during the coming weeks
corresponds with the epidemiological data collected in West Europe
during the 2 disease seasons since the introduction of BTV-8 in
summer 2006: the peak of cases appeared between September and October.

The EU map of BTV restriction zones was updated on 4 Sep 2008 and is
available at
<http://ec.europa.eu/food/animal/diseases/controlmeasures/bluetongue_restrictedzones-map.jpg>.
Sweden's declared BTV-8 zone is not yet included. - Mod.AS]
